W. Craig Jelinek - Wikipedia





















 






W. Craig Jelinek

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search



W. Craig Jelinek


Born
1953 (age 63–64)


Nationality
American


Alma mater
San Diego State University


Occupation
CEO, Costco


Salary
$6.5 million (2016)[1]


Term
2012-


Predecessor
James Sinegal


W. Craig Jelinek (born 1953) is an American businessman, president and chief executive officer of Costco since 2012, when he succeeded the company's founder, James Sinegal.
Jelinek was born in 1953 and grew up near Los Angeles.[2]
He started his career working for FedMart.[2]
Jelinek joined Costco in 1984, and has been CEO since 2012.[1]
References[edit]



^ a b "Executive Profile: W. Craig Jelinek". Bloomberg. Retrieved 26 June 2015. 
^ a b "W Craig Jelinek". BoardroomInsiders. 








